doc.after: The region s distance from historical centers of power in the East and the celebrated frontier spirit of its settlers offer two clich s for explaining the region s independent heterogeneous politics Historically the West was the first region to see widespread women s suffrage California birthed both the property rights and conservation movements and spawned such phenomena as the Taxpayer Revolt and the Berkeley Free Speech Movement It has also produced three presidents Herbert Hoover Richard Nixon and Ronald Reagan
